        "text": "We know how scary and confusing it can be when you are injured in an auto accident through no fault of your own. We understand the stress that comes from dealing with insurance companies, medical bills, and lost income during your recovery. Our goal is to ease your stress and aggressively pursue the compensation you deserve.\n\nThe Richmond personal injury lawyers at Marks & Harrison thoroughly investigate car accident cases and consults with highly qualified experts in accident reconstruction. We can determine whether another driver’s speeding, distracted driving, drunk driving, fatigued driving, or other careless, reckless behavior caused your crash.\n\nWe can then seek fair compensation for your medical expenses, lost wages, pain, and suffering, and other damages by dealing directly with the insurance companies on your behalf. We can seek a financial recovery for you through the at-fault driver’s liability coverage and, if necessary, turn to your own uninsured/underinsured motorist (UM / UIM) coverage.\n\nOur Richmond car accident lawyers will strive to promptly resolve your case. We know the important role those funds can play in your ability to move forward after your accident. However, if the insurance companies refuse to make a full and fair settlement offer, we will be ready to fight for you in court.\n\nAs a preliminary step in your case, we can help you with getting your damaged vehicle repaired or replaced. We can also ensure that your medical care goes uninterrupted and meets your needs.\n\nWhen an insurance company representative contacts you, simply refer the insurer to your attorney at Marks & Harrison. We can take it from there. You focus on getting well.\n\nIn many ways, getting into an accident with a large commercial truck is different from other types of vehicle accidents. It is important to work with a lawyer who understands these important differences.\n\nAt Marks & Harrison, our personal injury attorneys in Richmond have many 