hen employers and their workers’ compensation insurers refuse to pay claims. It is important to get help from an attorney who will protect your rights.\n\nAt Marks & Harrison, our Virginia workers’ compensation lawyers can help if your workers’ compensation claim has been denied or if your employer’s workers’ compensation carrier is dragging its feet when it comes to paying the benefits you need and deserve.\n\nWe work with clients across a broad range of industries, including construction, manufacturing, and health care.\n\nIn addition to pursuing workers’ compensation benefits for you, we can explore all other legal options that may be available in your case.\n\nFor instance, if your injury or illness was caused by a non-employer “third party” such as a negligent driver or the manufacturer of defective equipment, we can help you with filing a personal injury or product liability claim.\n\nThe options available to you in these types of claims can go well beyond what workers’ compensation benefits cover, allowing you to recover all of your lost wages as well as pain and suffering damages.\n\nDon’t wait to take action: Get in touch with our nearby personal injury lawyers in Richmond today to get started on your case."
